
++++++++++This tool is only for creating new ssh users. Using it with existing user arguments will reset passwords++++++++++++


Script to create a user with ssh access (Run on Ubuntu server):

script1.sh needs an argument (username) to create a user with default password root.

It should be run in a linux/unix environment as follows:

sudo sh script1.sh [New-Username]

//Password defaults to root


where [New-Username] should be replaced by your desired user_name.


//This script also displays the current ssh status at the end
